, or find their nearest addiction services . ' The World Health Organisation estimates there are 3.3 million deaths each year as a result of harmful use of alcohol . Doctors warn long term alcohol misuse is a major risk factor for conditions including heart disease , stroke , liver disease , and certain cancers . The survey was carried out by Opinium Research . Almost a quarter -LRB- 23 per cent -RRB- considered alcohol to be more harmful to their health than smoking .